  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Resilience and Capacity of Flood Affectees in Sindh through Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR) Education Using Mobile Knowledge Resource Center (MKRC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. 15 Community focused DRR 2 day&#x2019;s trainings that involve men and women equally.  

First day activities will comprise of sessions on:

i. Basic understanding of disasters and its affect.

ii. Life Saving Bottles.

iii. Sand Bags.

iv. Boat Making.

v. Village mapping

Second day activities:

Community Vulnerability Risk Assessment 

2. 6 School focused DRR trainings 

3. Follow up</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Students, teachers, local authorities, community members</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to bring about improved DRR and climate change resilience in Thatta, Sindh which is a high risk region in Pakistan. Through a need assessment carried out it was found that communities were ill prepared to deal with the hazards and disasters to which their environment is increasingly vulnerable and showed limited understanding on disaster causes and the wider climatic context.  Similar results were found in the Sindh populations (Need Assessment Report, Umerkot, Sindh, 2012 by CWS-P/A).</narrative>
  </description>
